# Streamlit App Walkthrough (Accuracy & History)

## Summary
The app has been upgraded with improved accuracy algorithms and a real-time key history display.

## Accuracy Improvements
- **Debounce Logic**: Prevents accidental double-clicks. You must "release" a key (straighten finger) before pressing again.
- **Angle Thresholds**: 
    - **Click**: Curl finger < 160 degrees.
    - **Release**: Straighten finger > 170 degrees.
- **Debug Numbers**: The current angle of each finger is shown on screen to help you learn the trigger points.

## New Features
- **Key History**: A "Recent Notes" list appears on the webpage, showing the sequence of keys you've played.
- **Full 5-Finger Support**: Play chords and melodies with any finger.

## How to Run
```bash
./.venv/bin/streamlit run app.py
```
Open the URL shown in the terminal (usually http://localhost:8501).
